cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS 

This paper deals with the theoretical analysis of neural networks, specifically the benefits of depth in terms of the number of layers. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the approximation power of different types of nodes, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions convolutional networks, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks, indicating a possible connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses boosted decision trees, which are a type of ensemble learning method, suggesting a connection to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
